]\n|8 October 2009\n| 15\u20130\u20130\n|Condemning \"in the strongest terms\" a [[2009 Kabul Indian embassy attack|suicide bombing at the Indian embassy]] in Afghanistan\n|-\n|[[United Nations Security Council Resolution 1891|1891]]\n|13 October 2009\n| 15\u20130\u20130\n|Extending the mandate of the Panel of Experts in [[Sudan]] to monitor the arms embargo and sanctions until 15 October 2010.\n|-\n|[[United Nations Security Council Resolution 1892|1892]]\n|13 October 2009\n| 15\u20130\u20130\n|Renewing the mandate of [[United Nations Stabilization Mission in Haiti|United Nations Stabilization Mission in Haiti (MINUSTAH)]] until 15 October 2010.\n|-\n|[[United Nations Security Council Resolution 1893|1893]]\n|29 October 2009\n| 15\u20130\u20130\n|Renewing measures on arms, financial and travel, banning importation of rough diamonds from [[C\u00f4te d'Ivoire]], extending mandate of Group of Experts until 31 October 2010.\n|-\n|[[United Nations Security Council Resolution 1894|1894]]\n|11 November 2009\n| 15\u20130\u20130\n|Calling on member states to respect human rights of civilians in armed conflict, and to act according to international law.\n|-\n|[[United Nations Security Council Resolution 1895|1895]]\n|18 November 2009\n| 15\u20130\u20130\n|Authorisation of member states to establish for a further 12 months a multinational stabilization force ([[EUFOR]]) in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] to succeed [[SFOR]].\n|-\n|[[United Nations Security Council Resolution 1896|1896]]\n|30 November 2009\n| 15\u20130\u20130\n|Extending the mandate of the Committee established pursuant to resolution 1533 (2004) and extension of measures on arms, transport, financial and travel against the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] imposed by resolution 1807 (2008).\n|-\n|[[United Nations Security Council Resolution 1897|1897]]\n|30 November 2009\n| 15\u20130\u20130\n|On acts of [[Piracy in Somalia|piracy and armed robbery]] against vessels in the waters off the coast of Somalia.\n|-\n|[